<HEAD>Actor-Dancer Tucker Smith Dies of Cancer at 52</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tucker Smith, who played the Jets gang's cool
lieutenant Ice in the Oscar winning movie ``West Side Story,'' has
died. He was 52.
   The actor-dancer died from neck and jaw cancer Thursday at the
UCLA Medical Center, said his publicist, Frank Liberman.
   After the landmark 1961 movie, which won 10 Oscars, Smith joined
the stage version of the musical in New York and Tokyo, said
Liberman.
   He also appeared in the films ``Hearts of the West'' and ``To Be
or Not to Be.'' His stage credits included ``Parade'' with Michelle
Lee, ``Vintage 60,'' and ``Anyone Can Whistle'' with Angela Lansbury
and Lee Remick.
   He also toured internationally with his own nightclub act.
   He is survived by three daughters.
