<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--WhiteChristmas     12-24 0176</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--White Christmas,0180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Seize Nativity Scene Of Cocaine Worth $2 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four Colombian men were arrested after
police made an unusual holiday haul _ a 12-figure nativity scene
filled with pressed cocaine worth $2 million.
   Police said Saturday that drug agents had discovered 6.6 pounds
of the drug inside figures including the infant Jesus, the Virgin
Mary, the three Kings and little lambs.
   The seizure and arrests capped a three-month surveillance of a
Colombian man suspected of being a major contact in drug-smuggling
operations into Madrid's Barajas Airport, police said.
   They said agents followed the man to the airport Thursday, where
they said he met a suspected drug courier arriving on a flight from
Bogota, Colombia.
   According to agents, the men went to an apartment in Madrid where
police later discovered the nativity scene along with $52,631 in
cash, which they also seized.
   Police said Luis Eduardo Fernandez Quijano, 21, and Jorge Enrique
Restrepo Jaramillo, 49, were arrested on drug-trafficking charges
along with two other men who were not identified.
</TEXT>
