<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Spain-Violence     12-24 0174</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Spain-Violence,0183</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Basque Separatists Claim Four Terrorist Attacks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SEBASTIAN, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Basque separatist group ETA
claimed responsibility for three bombings and a fatal shooting in
the past week, a newspaper reported Saturday.
   In a statement in the Basque daily Egin, the group said it bombed
a Civil Guard barracks Friday in the northern town of Alsasua,
seriously injuring one guard.
   The group said it planted another bomb near the Basque town of
Areta on Friday that damaged several Civil Guard vehicles and
slightly injured one guard and a bystander.
   ETA said it also was responsible for the attack Thursday in the
northern town of Zarauz in which a gunman killed a bar owner.
   The group also claimed the bombing Sunday of police vehicles in
which one officer was killed and 15 people were injured in the town
of Eibar.
   The group has been waging a 20-year campaign for a homeland in
the northern Basque region. Since 1968, ETA has claimed
responsibility for attacks that have killed more than 600 people.
</TEXT>
