<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ConvenienceStripper     12-24 0345</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Convenience Stripper,0353</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Arrested After Stripping in Store's Candy Aisle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ABILENE, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A convenience store clerk was treated to a
little adult entertainment when a man stripped down to a G-string
and leather jacket and bumped and ground his way down the candy
aisle.
   Circle K clerk Annette Ochoa said a man entered the store about 3
a.m. Friday and asked if he could use the restroom. She told him
this wasn't permitted to customers, and the man smiled and left.
   But minutes later he returned while she was talking on the phone.
   ``When I looked up, he was standing there with nothing but a
G-string and leather jacket on,'' Ochoa said. ``I told my friend,
`I've got a stripper, I'll have to call the cops.'''
   Once the stripper had her attention, he began performing.
   ``He walked up, picked up a Thrifty Nickel (newspaper) and did
some pumping motions, if you know what I mean,'' Ochoa said.
   ``Then he went down one aisle and then came up the candy aisle
and stood in front of the candy counter and did some more of his
motions. He heard me say I was calling the police, but he just stood
there until I dialed the numbers. Then he left.''
   The stripper didn't know when to quit his act though. He was
arrested on a complaint of indecent exposure shortly after he
appeared outside another convenience store. He was released without
any charge being filed, but police are still investigating.
   ``I was talking to my friend (at a second store) when she spotted
the guy walking around outside her store,'' Ochoa said. ``About that
time a cop walked in to ask me some follow-up questions and I told
him what was going on. He radioed it in and a cop who was nearby
caught him near the store on Lakeshore Drive. He was only wearing
his G-string and a leather jacket.''
   Ochoa says the strip show was something of a shock. Still, she
believes something good came from his performance.
   ``It kept me awake.''
</TEXT>
