<1ST_LINE>r a AM-CongressmanSideswiped     12-24 0186</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Congressman Sideswiped,0191</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Congressman Chases Down Cyclist Who Allegedly Hit His Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIMI VALLEY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rep. Elton Gallegly got the chance to
be a traffic cop when he chased down a motorcyclist who sideswiped
his new car, then held the man until police arrived.
   Roy Kinman, 43, of Moorpark was arrested for investigation of
driving under the influence of alcohol and hit-and-run driving,
police said.
   Gallegly, R-Calif., said he was waiting at a traffic light Friday
afternoon when his 1989 Mercury Cougar was hit by the cycle.
   ``He clipped the front part of my car,'' Gallegly said. ``He was
skidding in between three or four cars at the signal. I laid on my
horn and took off after him. I picked up the car phone and called
the police.''
   Gallegly said he gave chase until the cyclist became stuck in
traffic and finally pulled over.
   ``I told him, `You hit my car.' He said, `I didn't think I hit it
that hard,''' Gallegly said.
   Gallegly, a former Simi Valley mayor, had returned to this city
for the holidays while Congress is in recess.
</TEXT>
