<HEAD>Japan's Prime Minister Postpones U.S. Visit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister Noboru Takeshita has put off a visit
to Washington in early January to bid farewell to President Reagan
and meet his successor, reports said Saturday.
   Takeshita was quoted in news reports saying Friday that his trip,
scheduled for Jan. 5-9, will be postponed to March or later.
   He said the postponement would give him time to work on putting
into effect a 1989 tax reform package.
   The prime minister had said earlier he wanted to meet Reagan and
greet President-elect George Bush.
